==== OPTION A: Using Docker containers
  
0) Mount the `janus` path on your local file system
by updating the `run_container.sh` script (change the `/c/uni_work/...`
to the path on your system).

1) Start a Docker container;

$ ./run_container.sh

2) Create build directory: 
$ mkdir build

3) Run CMake: 

$ cd build && cmake .. && cd ..
  
4) Compile:

$ ./run_make

5) From inside Docker container, run e.g:

$ ./janus/jdsl_run <your_binary>

(Make sure you have at least 2 cores available,
otherwise remove `taskset --cpu-list 1-2` from the jdsl_run script)

==== OPTION B: Without Docker containers

A Docker container is not required, you can run this directly if you use Linux.
																	     ~                                                           
